Louis Jordan was rescued from a disabled sailboat off the North Carolina coast on Thursday . 
  Jordan, 37, released a three-paragraph statement on Monday in which he said he stayed inside his cabin to keep dry and avoid sun, wind, waves and sea spray during his ordeal . 
  He said he rationed food and water and kept his calorie expenditure low . 
  Jordan was spotted by a German-flagged boat on Thursday after sailing out of a South Carolina marina . 
 